    <p>TURIN • Ju­ven­tus cap­tain Leonardo Bonucci has apol­o­gised to the club’s fans for both his and his team’s woe­ful dis­play in their 3-0 Serie A home de­feat by Fiorentina. His mis­takes led di­rectly to two goals on Tues­day and he also gifted their ri­vals sev­eral other chances.</p>
    <p>Du­san Vla­hovic opened the scor­ing be­fore Juan Cuadrado was shown a straight red card for a dan­ger­ous tackle and the vis­i­tors took ad­van­tage via an own goal by Alex San­dro and Martin Cac­eres.</p>
    <p>The cham­pi­ons’ first league de­feat this sea­son left them fourth with 24 points af­ter 13 games, seven be­hind lead­ers AC Mi­lan.</p>


